<p>Good morning,  I have an e-commerce website and due to italian rules about vat indication, I set the functions.php in order to require as mandatory the VAT number during sign-up. The code used is the following (which I paste, in case someone needs it):</p>  <pre><code> function custom_colors() {    echo '&lt;style type="text/css"&gt;         ._billing_cf_field{clear: both!important;width: 100%!important;}    &lt;/style&gt;'; } add_action('admin_head', 'custom_colors');  add_filter( 'woocommerce_billing_fields' , 'billing_field_cfpiva' );  function billing_field_cfpiva( $fields ) { $fields['cf'] = array( 'label' =&gt; __('Codice Fiscale / P.IVA', 'woocommerce'), 'show' =&gt; true ); return $fields; }  add_action('woocommerce_created_customer',        'admin_email_on_registration', 10 , 1); function admin_email_on_registration( $customer_id) { wp_new_user_notification( $customer_id ); } </code></pre>  <p>Now, this shows the field for VAT number (Partita IVA) as mandatory in the registration page, as you can see here: <a href="http://www.calzaturediffusionelino.it/mio-account/" rel="nofollow">http://www.calzaturediffusionelino.it/mio-account/</a></p>  <p>What I need to do, is to show the VAT number provided during registration in the User Profile page, because only retailers can register to the website and admins have to check if the user is a retailer before they can approve her. Does someone know how can I do that?</p>  <p>Thanks!</p>